OL,7,F"Disabled parents, children, and
OL,8,Fcarers frequently find themselves
OL,9,Funable to endure long waits due to
OL,10,Fchronic pain, sensory sensitivities,
OL,11,For neurodivergent conditions like
OL,12,Fanxiety, heightened noise sensitivity,
OL,13,Fand discomfort in crowded spaces.
OL,15,F"For many, the option to access a
OL,16,Fspeedy pass is not just a convenience
OL,17,Fbut a crucial accommodation that
OL,18,Fenables participation in activities
OL,19,Fthat others take for granted.
